sentences.en: A highly localized, specialized piece of substrate is densely overgrown.
sentences.cn: 菌体稠密地长满了一小块高度局限的特化的基质上.

sentences.en: A slash is usually overgrown with bushes or trees.
sentences.cn: 沼泽低地通常是灌木丛生或长满树木.

sentences.en: As the equipment was unpacked, I led Lee around the overgrown garden.
sentences.cn: 取出设备后，我带着李在花草蔓生的花园里转了一圈。

sentences.en: Daphne Farlow, at forty-five, still looked and spoke like an overgrown schoolgirl.
sentences.cn: 45岁的达芙妮·法洛外貌言谈都还像个稚气未脱的小女生。

sentences.en: Much of the track had become overgrown with hawthorn.
sentences.cn: 小路上很多地方都长满了山楂树。

sentences.en: Now and then he picked raspberries in the overgrown garden.
sentences.cn: 有时,他会跑到杂草丛生的花园里去采摘蔗莓.

sentences.en: Now and then he picked raspnerries in the overgrown garden.
sentences.cn: 有时,他会跑到杂草丛生的花园里去采摘悬白子.

sentences.en: Overgrown deciduous shrubs can be cut back at this time of year.
sentences.cn: 过于繁茂的落叶灌木可以在每年的这个时候修剪.

sentences.en: The garden of the empty house is overgrown with weeds.
sentences.cn: 这座空房子的花园里长满了杂草.

sentences.en: The garden's completely overgrown with weeds.
The river banks were overgrown with reed.
The spade sank into a clump of overgrown bushes.
sentences.cn: 铲子插入了一丛长势旺盛的灌木丛。

sentences.en: The yard was overgrown with weeds.
This bleak place overgrown with nettles was the churchyard.
sentences.cn: 那蔓草丛生的凄凉地方是教堂公墓.

sentences.en: When I came back from my long vacation, I found my garden overgrown.
sentences.cn: 当度完长假归来时, 我发现我的花园里杂草丛生.

words.tran_cn: 增生；繁茂；生长过度；过度发育

trans.tran_cn: 长得很快的，杂草丛生的
trans.tran_en: covered with plants that have grown in an uncontrolled way
